text: Warmian-Masurian Voivodeship is a voivodeship (province) in Poland. Its capital and largest city is Olsztyn. It was created on January 1, 1999. ==Protected areas== Protected areas in Warmian-Masurian Voivodeship include 8 Landscape Parks, as listed below: * Brodnica Landscape Park (partly in Kuyavian-Pomeranian Voivodeship) * Dylewo Hills Landscape Park * Elbląg Upland Landscape Park * Górzno-Lidzbark Landscape Park (partly in Kuyavian-Pomeranian and Masovian Voivodeships) * Iława Lake District Landscape Park (partly in Pomeranian Voivodeship) * Masurian Landscape Park * Puszcza Romincka Landscape Park * Wel Landscape Park The Łuknajno Lake nature reserve is a protected wetland site under the Ramsar convention. It is also a UNESCO biosphere reserve. Category:1999 establishments in Poland
title: Warmian-Masurian Voivodeship
